task.summary: MarkdownDoc-1 Fails to resolve document relative path to images.
- Added insert image function. - Fixed bug in settings function that failed to apply settings if no setting file were saved.
- Added InsertLinkFunction. - SaveFunction now opens save dialog!
SaveFunction now only shows .md and .markdown files in save dialog.
- SaveFunction now only shows .md and .markdown files in save dialog. - Copy, cut, and paste functions have been commented out since JEditorPane seems to handle this itself now.
Refactored configuration so that configs are static, but config changed callbacks are per editor window instance. That is, any change to config will affect all open windows.
Bug fix: When settings window were closed by clicking window close button rather than cancel or save neither of these operations were done. Now it is the same as cancel.

- Added PersistentProps API (available from Editor) for loading and saving properties files under {user home}/.markdownDoc. - Finished ExportToPDFFunction, which now also saves the latest generation information for reuse the next time. This uses PersistentProps. - SaveFunction and OpenFunction now also used PersistentProps to save window postition and size on save and reset it on load per filename of edited files.

Saving settings now also saves the window size and position. If there is no known filename at time of settings save, then size and positions is saved as "default" and will thus be loaded and used when a new empty editor window is opened.
Now also exports to html.
- Added support for list bullet indent level change in both directions with tab and shift-tab. - Ran CodeLicenseManager "apply" to insert/update license header information in source files.
The editor is now packaged as: - A clickable, executable Jar file. - A Mac OS X App in a .dmg file.
- Debugged. - Added editor docs.
Added configurable margins.
Now only allows heading to be one line (up to LF/CRLF). Heading where treated like paragraphs before. This change is to be compatible with other Markdown tools.

Added markdown file reading feature by dropping markdown files on editor in preview mode. This will format and show the dropped file without changing the content of the editor. Exiting preview mode will bring you back to the editor content and entering preview mode again will again preview the editor content.
Updated pom.xml to support release to maven central.
Updated pom.xml to support release to maven central.
Updated doc to say that version 1.2.9 is now in maven central.
Updated readme to indicate that version 1.2.9 is now in maven central.
